      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(security): escape field names in transcript regex extraction",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`extractJsonStringFieldPrefix` and `extractJsonNullableStringFieldPrefix` in `session-utils.fs.ts` interpolate the `field` parameter directly into `new RegExp(...)` without escaping. All current callers pass hardcoded field names (`\"id\"`, `\"parentId\"`, `\"type\"`, `\"role\"`), but the function signature accepts any `string`. A future caller passing a field containing regex metacharacters (e.g. `\"foo.bar\"`) would match unintended patterns (`.` matches any character instead of a literal dot).\n\nThis wraps the interpolation with `escapeRegExp()` from `src/shared/regexp.ts` so metacharacters are treated literally.\n\n## Verification\n\n219 session-utils tests pass (gateway-core, gateway-server, gateway-client). The new `oversized line metadata extraction preserves id and parentId` test exercises the escapeRegExp-guarded regex path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Regex injection via unescaped field name interpolation in oversized transcript metadata extraction (`session-utils.fs.ts:276,293`). Metacharacter field names cause extraction failure or wrong-value extraction.\n\n**Real environment tested:** macOS arm64, Node 26.0.0, openclaw checkout at patched head.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nStandalone runtime script that replicates the vulnerable and fixed extraction functions, then runs each against JSON prefixes containing field names with regex metacharacters:\n\n```\nnode --import tsx /tmp/proof-85934.mjs\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```\n=== PR #85934: field name regex escape proof ===\n\nField with parentheses: count(items)\n  Input: {\"count(items)\":\"5\",\"other\":\"x\"}\n  Before fix: EXTRACTION FAILED\n  After fix:  5\n\nField with brackets: tags[0]\n  Input: {\"tags[0]\":\"first\",\"tags0x\":\"other\"}\n  Before fix: EXTRACTION FAILED\n  After fix:  first\n\nField with plus: rate+tax\n  Input: {\"rate+tax\":\"15\",\"ratetax\":\"10\"}\n  Before fix: 10\n  After fix:  15\n\nField with $: $ref\n  Input: {\"$ref\":\"#/definitions/model\",\"ref\":\"fallback\"}\n  Before fix: EXTRACTION FAILED\n  After fix:  #/definitions/model\n\nSafe field name (normal transcript): id\n  Input: {\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"msg-abc123\",\"parentId\":\"root\"}\n  Before fix: msg-abc123\n  After fix:  msg-abc123\n  Both work correctly for safe field names.\n\nescapeRegExp neutralizes metacharacters while safe names are unaffected.\n```\n\nWithout escapeRegExp, parentheses, brackets, and dollar signs cause extraction to fail entirely, and the plus sign causes extraction of the wrong value (`10` from `\"ratetax\"` instead of `15` from `\"rate+tax\"`). With escapeRegExp, all metacharacter field names are treated literally and extract the correct value.\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The escapeRegExp wrapper fixes four classes of metacharacter failures (parentheses, brackets, plus, dollar sign) while leaving safe field names unaffected. The plus-sign case is the most dangerous: it silently returns the wrong value instead of failing.\n\n**What was not tested:** End-to-end production transcript pipeline with adversarial field names (all current callers use hardcoded safe strings). The fix is defense-in-depth.\n",
        "branch": "fix/session-utils-regex-escape",
